===Etymology===
From [[push]], to sell or promote plus [[poll]], survey
===Noun===
'''push poll'''
#a [[campaign]] technique in which a [[fake]] poll is used to alter the views of [[respondent]]s. Push polls are generally viewed as form of [[negative]] campaigning. The term is also sometimes used incorrectly to refer to actual polls which test political messages, some of which may be negative. 
